    "body": "That's fair! I just personally think that not including the lock file makes more sense for a template (we take that approach in hardhat sample projects, for example). It means less maintenance and that users always get the latest versions of the dependencies.\n\nThe only downside I see is that a dependency that doesn't follow semver can cause problems, but if that happens you can pin it in the package.json.\n\nOf course, it's your template, you can do whatever you think is better ðŸ™‚",
